    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-06-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-06-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="197" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                <head>No. 193.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">L.
                                    West</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-06-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 15, 1886</date>.
                                [Received June 16.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of yesterday’s date, bringing to my notice certain
                            alleged warnings given <pb facs="0468" n="384" xml:id="pg_384"/> by the
                            Canadian authorities to American fishing vessels, and to inform you that
                            I have brought the matter to the notice of Her Majesty’s Government.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>L. S. SACKVILLE WEST.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
